A future post-beta licensing structure is planned and may differ from the current licensing.

At that time, the project is intended to adopt a mixed-license model, with components potentially including AGPLv3, LGPLv3, MPL-2.0, and Creative Commons Attribution 4.0, depending on subsystem.

The intended structure (post-beta) is documented in detail under the LICENSES/ directory and related documentation.

Generated code produced by this project is exempt from the AGPL-3.0-only license, except where such code embeds compiler internals, ships substantial implementation components, or directly incorporates internal (non-public) APIs or modules of the project.

Use of documented public APIs does not, by itself, create a derivative work under the AGPL-3.0-only license.

All APIs and implementation components are classified as either public or internal. This classification is documented in the codebase and is intended to define licensing and usage boundaries.

